description: List queued messages in the downlink queue.

parameters.name: Id
parameters.description: The ID of a given wireless device which the downlink message packets are being sent.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: To retrieve the next set of results, the nextToken value from a previous response; otherwise null to receive the first set of results.

nested_items.name: DownlinkQueueMessagesList
nested_items.description: The messages in the downlink queue.

nested_items.name: MessageId
nested_items.description: The message ID assigned by IoT Wireless to each downlink message, which helps identify the message.

nested_items.name: TransmitMode
nested_items.description: The transmit mode to use for sending data to the wireless device. This can be 0 for UM (unacknowledge mode) or 1 for AM (acknowledge mode).

nested_items.name: ReceivedAt
nested_items.description: The time at which Iot Wireless received the downlink message.

nested_items.name: ParticipatingGateways
nested_items.description: Choose the gateways that you want to use for the downlink data traffic when the wireless device is running in class B or class C mode.

nested_items.name: DownlinkMode
nested_items.description: Indicates whether to send the downlink message in sequential mode or concurrent mode, or to use only the chosen gateways from the previous uplink message transmission.

nested_items.name: GatewayList
nested_items.description: The list of gateways that you want to use for sending the downlink data traffic.

nested_items.name: GatewayId
nested_items.description: The ID of the wireless gateways that you want to add to the list of gateways when sending downlink messages.

nested_items.name: DownlinkFrequency
nested_items.description: The frequency to use for the gateways when sending a downlink message to the wireless device.

nested_items.name: TransmissionInterval
nested_items.description: The duration of time for which AWS IoT Core for LoRaWAN will wait before transmitting the payload to the next gateway.
